HEADWORD: Maturation
<hw>Mat`u*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>maturatio</ets> a hastening: cf. F. <ets>maturation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The process of bringing, or of coming, to maturity; hence,
specifically, the process of suppurating perfectly; the formation of pus
or matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maturative</ent>⟦br⟧
